# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your Python version
#   with the team or users by checking in .python-version.
#   However, for standard application templates, we might ignore this.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're executing Pipenv inside a virtualenv, you may need to ignore it.
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similarly, Check-in poetry.lock unless you have a good reason not to.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv and Poetry, check-in pdm.lock unless you have a good reason not to.
# pdm.lock

# virtualenv
#   It is strongly recommended to exclude virtual environments from Git.
